==English==

===Etymology===
[[Category:Greek derivations]]
From French [[numismatique]], from Late [[Latin]] [[numisma]], [[numismatis]], "coin", variant of Latin [[nomisma]], from [[Ancient Greek]] '''[[νόμισμα]]''' (''nomisma'') "current coin, custom", from '''[[νομίζω]]''' (''nomizo'') "to hold or own as a custom, usage, to use customarily, practise, to be used to a thing", hence "to make common use of", from '''[[νόμος]]''' (''nomos'') "usage, custom", from '''[[νέμω]]''' (''nemo'') "to keep, to hold, to watch"

(See base *nem- in Indo-European Roots)

===Pronunciation===
nmz-mtk, -ms-, ny-

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''numismatics'''
nu·mis·mat·ic    
# The study of [[coin]]s.
# Of or relating to coins or [[currency]]. 
# Of or relating to numismatics.

